40|$|We {{carry out}} finite-difference time-domain (FDTD) simulations, with a specially-designed {{boundary}} condition, on pure <b>evanescent</b> <b>waves</b> interacting with a lossy left-handed material (LHM) slab. Our results provide the first full-wave numerical {{evidence for the}} amplification of <b>evanescent</b> <b>waves</b> inside a LHM slab of finite absorption. The amplification {{is due to the}} interactions between the <b>evanescent</b> <b>waves</b> and the coupled surface polaritons at the two surfaces of the LHM slab and the physical process can be described by a simple model. Comment: 4 pages, 2 figure...|$|R
